title: No. 998 Fifth Avenue. Northeast Corner Eighty-first Street.

text:
998 Fifth Avenue at N.E. corner of 81st Street, one of the early apartment houses on Fifth Avenue.
About 1912.

Fifth Ave., east side, north from and including 81st, to, but not including 82nd Streets.

1928.

capitol Photo Service.

No. 1006 Fifth Avenue, the small white building adjoining the modern apartment house, is to be converted into a 6 story educational structure by the present owners, the American Museum of Natural History, according to plans filed, as reported in the New York Sun of June 3, 1938.
